  "texts": [
    "In this work, we only use the MRS spectra with v sin i less than 30 km/s, i.e., the spectra with vsini lasp = -9999.0.",
    "This condition has been quantitatively evaluated for the Hα line data of MRS in He et al (2023).",
    "The spectra that do not meet the condition are removed from our sample.",
    "The H II regions are a type of Galactic nebulae ionized by the ultraviolet radiations from nearby young massive stars, and have strong Hα signals (e.g., Peimbert et al 2017; Pérez-Montero 2017; Wu et al 2021).",
    "If the observed stellar objects are close to or located in the H II regions, the stellar Hα fluxes may be contaminated with the signals from the H II regions."
  ],
